The situation is turbulent.

27
00:02:49,190 --> 00:02:51,190
We'd better not hold a public trial.

28
00:02:52,470 --> 00:02:54,470
What should we do?

29
00:02:55,840 --> 00:02:59,030
Extreme times call for extreme measures.

30
00:03:00,030 --> 00:03:01,290
Shall we kill them all?

31
00:03:02,030 --> 00:03:03,190
Don't kill them all.

32
00:03:03,680 --> 00:03:05,410
But don't free them all either.

33
00:03:06,680 --> 00:03:09,590
Let them bet on their own luck.

34
00:03:29,210 --> 00:03:36,470
[Youth of Banner Battalion, Liang Xiang]
[Courtesy name: Tufang]

35
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:43,970
What's this?

36
00:03:44,190 --> 00:03:44,590
Are you

37
00:03:44,590 --> 00:03:45,990
beheading people today?

38
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:47,520
Go away.

39
00:03:48,030 --> 00:03:48,960
Kid,

40
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:50,470
why are you here?

41
00:03:50,840 --> 00:03:52,170
Why aren't you in class?

42
00:03:52,360 --> 00:03:53,560
The teacher canceled our class today.

43
00:03:53,560 --> 00:03:55,440
He said something was happening here.

44
00:03:55,440 --> 00:03:56,750
I borrowed my third cousin's horse.

45
00:03:56,750 --> 00:03:58,480
It was fast, so I got here first.

46
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:00,960
This is such a sinister thing.

47
00:04:00,960 --> 00:04:03,020
A kid like you shouldn't spectate it.

48
00:04:03,360 --> 00:04:05,560
You just might get possessed by a ghost.

49
00:04:06,560 --> 00:04:07,750
If you're not afraid,

50
00:04:07,750 --> 00:04:08,810
what am I afraid of?

51
00:04:25,310 --> 00:04:28,170
Beheading people is a sinister and unlucky matter.

52
00:04:28,340 --> 00:04:29,260
Normally,

53
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:30,920
you should choose to do it

54
00:04:30,920 --> 00:04:33,040
when the sun is the strongest.

55
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:34,600
At the very least,

56
00:04:36,380 --> 00:04:38,159
the sun should be right above our heads.

57
00:04:38,159 --> 00:04:39,620
Look at the weather today.

58
00:04:40,720 --> 00:04:42,159
It's ominous.

59
00:04:50,190 --> 00:04:52,120
Three-quarters past noon is here.

60
00:05:38,159 --> 00:05:38,960
Double round.

61
00:05:39,600 --> 00:05:40,360
Behead him!

62
00:05:48,270 --> 00:05:49,159
Kneel!

63
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:07,350
Next.

64
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:16,410
Move.

65
00:06:24,160 --> 00:06:25,270
What's your name?

66
00:06:30,430 --> 00:06:31,430
Yang Aiguo.

67
00:06:36,870 --> 00:06:37,750
How old are you?

68
00:06:38,390 --> 00:06:39,270
Seventeen.

69
00:06:41,390 --> 00:06:43,720
You're rebelling at the age of seventeen?

70
00:06:46,250 --> 00:06:47,610
What a pity.

71
00:06:55,350 --> 00:06:56,200
Kneel!

72
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:02,180
It's just a gamble.

73
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:03,850
The bet is your life.

74
00:07:05,360 --> 00:07:06,120
Don't panic.

75
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:09,480
You have two-thirds of the chance.

76
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:11,960
If you get one flat and one round,

77
00:07:12,190 --> 00:07:13,320
you'll be released.

78
00:07:15,480 --> 00:07:18,140
If you get double flat, you'll also be released.

79
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:20,720
Only if you get a double round

80
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:22,120
will you be beheaded.

81
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:25,950
Your toss determines your life.

82
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:28,950
Throw it well.

83
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:12,820
One flat and one round.

84
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:14,560
Released.

85
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:21,560
What are you waiting for?

86
00:08:21,560 --> 00:08:22,190
Go!

87
00:08:24,770 --> 00:08:25,570
Drag him away.

88
00:08:29,720 --> 00:08:30,480
Next.

89
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:53,840
Hurry up, go home.

90
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:55,370
You are so lucky.

91
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:58,360
I'm afraid others won't have such good luck.

92
00:08:58,360 --> 00:08:59,080
Get up.

93
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:04,090
Let me send you back.

94
00:09:04,120 --> 00:09:05,960
I'm familiar with the soldiers of the Banner Battalion.

95
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:07,200
If anyone catches you again,

96
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:08,460
I will speak up for you.

97
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:09,610
Let's go.

98
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:27,420
[Hubei, Jingzhou]

99
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:21,390
Slow down.

100
00:09:21,510 --> 00:09:23,440
You're going too fast. It's scary.

101
00:09:23,720 --> 00:09:25,790
This land belongs to the Qing Dynasty.

102
00:09:25,790 --> 00:09:27,320
You dared to rebel

103
00:09:27,540 --> 00:09:28,660
at such a young age.

104
00:09:28,870 --> 00:09:30,120
But you're scared

105
00:09:30,120 --> 00:09:31,250
of a fast horse ride?

106
00:09:31,390 --> 00:09:33,050
I feel dizzy if I ride too fast.

107
00:09:33,910 --> 00:09:35,790
Okay, I'll ride slowly.

108
00:09:36,750 --> 00:09:38,080
I'll be honest with you.

109
00:09:38,150 --> 00:09:39,080
I skipped class today

110
00:09:39,080 --> 00:09:40,610
to spectate the beheading.

111
00:09:40,910 --> 00:09:43,110
My master will scold me if I go back late.

112
00:09:43,150 --> 00:09:44,880
You're not a soldier yourself?

113
00:09:45,390 --> 00:09:46,480
Us Bannermen

114
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:48,630
are reservists as soon as we're born.

115
00:09:48,630 --> 00:09:50,480
But you have to be 18 to be a soldier.

116
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:51,740
I'm one year too young.

117
00:09:52,960 --> 00:09:54,010
You're also 17?

118
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:57,150
That's right. We're the same age.

119
00:10:04,150 --> 00:10:05,960
Liang, why are you here?

120
00:10:05,980 --> 00:10:07,790
Uncle, I have a class to attend.

121
00:10:07,960 --> 00:10:08,720
I'm leaving.

122
00:10:08,840 --> 00:10:10,550
Be careful. Don't fall down.

123
00:10:27,190 --> 00:10:27,910
Thanks.

124
00:10:28,330 --> 00:10:29,260
You're welcome.

125
00:10:40,150 --> 00:10:43,840
When order is lost, benevolence and righteousness arise.

126
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:48,150
When wisdom and intelligence emerge, so does deception.

127
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:52,600
When family ties are broken, there arises filial piety and compassion.

128
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:56,840
In times of national crisis, there emerge loyal ministers.

129
00:10:57,400 --> 00:11:01,880
Abandoning sacredness and cleverness will benefit the people a hundredfold.

130
00:11:01,910 --> 00:11:06,700
Abandoning benevolence and righteousness will restore the people's filial nature.

131
00:11:06,700 --> 00:11:11,580
Abandoning deceit and profit will eliminate thieves and robbers.

132
00:11:13,960 --> 00:11:15,050
Where did you go?

133
00:11:22,390 --> 00:11:24,480
The rebels were being executed outside the city. So I...

134
00:11:24,480 --> 00:11:25,390
Kneel!

135
00:11:29,170 --> 00:11:30,830
Didn't the rest of you say that

136
00:11:30,840 --> 00:11:32,720
he went home to get brush and ink?

137
00:11:34,960 --> 00:11:37,270
All of you, kneel down!

138
00:11:38,080 --> 00:11:38,720
Kneel!

139
00:11:47,120 --> 00:11:51,120
When family ties are broken, there arises filial piety and compassion.

140
00:11:51,150 --> 00:11:54,480
In times of national crisis, there emerge loyal ministers.

141
00:11:54,510 --> 00:11:55,910
But what about all of you?

142
00:11:57,480 --> 00:11:59,390
Don't you have any sense of

143
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:01,790
filial piety and loyalty?

144
00:12:14,910 --> 00:12:19,960
The horses are back.

145
00:12:19,570 --> 00:12:23,090
[Jingzhou Banner Battalion]

146
00:12:23,020 --> 00:12:23,900
Don't touch me!

147
00:12:24,390 --> 00:12:25,390
Don't touch me!

148
00:12:26,790 --> 00:12:28,250
Slow down. Don't touch me.

149
00:12:28,270 --> 00:12:29,360
If my mother sees me

150
00:12:29,630 --> 00:12:30,790
with this bowl of water,

151
00:12:30,790 --> 00:12:32,120
she'll beat me for sure.

152
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:34,600
It’s Liang Xiang's fault.

153
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:36,460
You are the culprit, Liang Xiang.

154
00:12:37,960 --> 00:12:39,030
Want to bet

155
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:39,790
if I dare to

156
00:12:39,790 --> 00:12:41,990
carry this bowl of water back on my head?

157
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:44,080
No way. I think you can't.

158
00:12:44,840 --> 00:12:45,600
Master won't forgive you

159
00:12:45,600 --> 00:12:46,630
if you spill the water.

160
00:12:46,630 --> 00:12:48,960
That's right, he won't forgive you.

161
00:12:49,390 --> 00:12:51,270
There you go again.

162
00:12:51,570 --> 00:12:52,690
Look at all of you.

163
00:12:52,720 --> 00:12:53,390
What should we do

164
00:12:53,390 --> 00:12:54,960
with you lot in the future?

165
00:12:57,030 --> 00:12:59,190
If I go back with this bowl of water on my head,

166
00:12:59,190 --> 00:13:00,200
what will you give me for losing the bet?

167
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:01,200
If you can do that,

168
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:02,090
we'll treat you

169
00:13:02,090 --> 00:13:03,450
to 20 fried fritters.

170
00:13:03,480 --> 00:13:04,680
Your words, not mine.

171
00:13:04,960 --> 00:13:05,840
Don't regret it.

172
00:13:05,840 --> 00:13:06,670
If you spill

173
00:13:06,670 --> 00:13:07,720
even a single drop,

174
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:08,720
you'll have to treat us

175
00:13:08,720 --> 00:13:09,390
to 20 fried fritters instead.

176
00:13:09,390 --> 00:13:10,080
Yes, that's right.

177
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:10,600
Twenty fried fritters.

178
00:13:10,600 --> 00:13:11,270
We'll report

179
00:13:11,270 --> 00:13:12,150
your failure to Master too.

180
00:13:12,150 --> 00:13:13,300
Let's make a bet then.

181
00:13:13,300 --> 00:13:14,110
Let's bet.

182
00:13:14,130 --> 00:13:14,650
Bet!

183
00:13:14,680 --> 00:13:15,530
Yes.

184
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:22,930
It's really on his head now.

185
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:25,480
Don't spill it.

186
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:27,080
Let's go home.

187
00:13:33,360 --> 00:13:34,120
Liang.

188
00:13:34,840 --> 00:13:36,840
You are really something.

189
00:13:39,960 --> 00:13:40,840
You brat.

190
00:13:42,480 --> 00:13:43,910
Look at all of you.

191
00:13:59,030 --> 00:14:00,600
Twenty fried fritters.

192
00:14:00,720 --> 00:14:01,390
Let's go home.

193
00:14:01,390 --> 00:14:02,790
Let's go.

194
00:14:11,790 --> 00:14:13,360
What did I tell you?

195
00:14:18,680 --> 00:14:20,410
Your father passed away early.

196
00:14:20,550 --> 00:14:22,240
You are my only hope.

197
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:25,510
Why can't you study hard

198
00:14:25,510 --> 00:14:26,840
and make me proud?

199
00:14:32,790 --> 00:14:33,600
I was wrong.

200
00:14:35,270 --> 00:14:36,080
Really?

201
00:14:37,370 --> 00:14:38,930
You're 17, going 18 soon.

202
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:40,930
You're an adult.

203
00:14:41,960 --> 00:14:43,620
You should learn to work hard.

204
00:14:46,320 --> 00:14:47,720
Are you going somewhere?

205
00:14:48,030 --> 00:14:50,430
Have dinner by yourself. It's on the stove.

206
00:14:50,630 --> 00:14:51,910
The magistrate's family has invited

207
00:14:51,910 --> 00:14:53,900
the Salt Transport Commissioner of Huguang's wife for dinner.

208
00:14:53,740 --> 00:14:59,050
[Descendant of Dorgon, Prince Rui, Mother of Liang]

209
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:55,510
Somehow, they found me

210
00:14:55,960 --> 00:14:57,620
and asked me to accompany her.

211
00:14:59,480 --> 00:15:01,280
I wonder what they are thinking.

212
00:15:44,080 --> 00:15:45,880
What am I supposed to do with you?

213
00:15:46,790 --> 00:15:48,850
Of all the things you could have done,

214
00:15:48,960 --> 00:15:50,560
why did you have to be a rebel?

215
00:16:00,030 --> 00:16:01,030
So beautiful.

216
00:16:01,550 --> 00:16:03,580
Your Liangbatou hairstyle is beautiful.

217
00:16:03,580 --> 00:16:05,510
What is this lousy official doing?

218
00:16:06,320 --> 00:16:07,240
It's so noisy.

219
00:16:07,480 --> 00:16:08,360
How do you Bannermen

220
00:16:08,360 --> 00:16:10,240
kowtow with so many

221
00:16:10,630 --> 00:16:12,080
accessories on your head?

222
00:16:11,100 --> 00:16:15,810
[Manistrate's Mansion of Jingzhou]

223
00:16:12,570 --> 00:16:14,790
The women in the old ancestral residence

224
00:16:14,790 --> 00:16:16,790
only kneel when they have to kowtow.

225
00:16:16,840 --> 00:16:18,030
We use our right hand

226
00:16:18,150 --> 00:16:19,950
to touch the tip of our Liangbatou.

227
00:16:19,950 --> 00:16:21,000
When we touch it,

228
00:16:21,150 --> 00:16:23,720
we tilt our head slightly to the right.

229
00:16:24,110 --> 00:16:26,350
One touch equals one kowtow.

230
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:28,600
For each kneel, we touch it 3 times.

231
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:30,930
If we kneel again, we touch it 3 more times.

232
00:16:31,240 --> 00:16:33,370
Could you demonstrate it for us to see?

233
00:16:33,910 --> 00:16:35,030
Just like this.

234
00:16:39,330 --> 00:16:40,210
It's so neat.

235
00:16:49,720 --> 00:16:50,960
It's so elegant.

236
00:16:51,030 --> 00:16:52,150
It's so neat.

237
00:16:53,080 --> 00:16:53,910
So beautiful.

238
00:16:57,080 --> 00:16:59,340
We have made the right call to invite you.

239
00:16:59,840 --> 00:17:02,150
The Salt Transport Commissioner's wife is also a Bannerman.

240
00:17:02,150 --> 00:17:04,160
I don't understand your rules.

241
00:17:04,480 --> 00:17:05,770
When she arrives later,

242
00:17:05,770 --> 00:17:07,450
you have to help me out.

243
00:17:07,480 --> 00:17:08,960
Make sure I don't make a mistake

244
00:17:08,960 --> 00:17:10,359
and make a fool of myself.

245
00:17:10,510 --> 00:17:11,640
Got it, Madam.

246
00:17:13,160 --> 00:17:14,589
This is my daughter, Duo Mei.

247
00:17:14,359 --> 00:17:17,369
[Duo Mei]

248
00:17:15,240 --> 00:17:16,750
Duo Mei, greet your aunt.

249
00:17:16,750 --> 00:17:17,480
Aunt.

250
00:17:17,750 --> 00:17:19,109
We Bannermen

251
00:17:19,349 --> 00:17:21,220
use "auntie" instead.

252
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:23,440
For example, the sixth auntie or

253
00:17:23,490 --> 00:17:24,970
the seventh auntie.

254
00:17:25,240 --> 00:17:27,640
We add their ranks in front of the address.

255
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:29,480
Would you look at that?

256
00:17:29,880 --> 00:17:31,880
I almost made another mistake.

257
00:17:33,350 --> 00:17:34,210
Later,

258
00:17:34,350 --> 00:17:36,000
when the wife of the Salt Transport Commissioner is here,

259
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:38,240
you can call her third auntie.

260
00:17:39,480 --> 00:17:42,160
Does a junior need to perform formal greetings too?

261
00:17:42,160 --> 00:17:43,160
Of course.

262
00:17:43,690 --> 00:17:46,320
Does she kneel on both knees

263
00:17:46,350 --> 00:17:47,910
or just one knee for the greeting?

264
00:17:47,910 --> 00:17:49,830
Men kneel on both knees.

265
00:17:50,400 --> 00:17:52,110
When ladies meet each other,

266
00:17:52,240 --> 00:17:54,030
they can just bend their knees instead.

267
00:17:54,030 --> 00:17:55,290
Just like this, Madam.

268
00:17:59,110 --> 00:17:59,790
Like this.

269
00:17:59,790 --> 00:18:01,240
It's such a neat greeting.

270
00:18:01,240 --> 00:18:02,110
I've never seen it before.

271
00:18:02,110 --> 00:18:02,960
This gesture.

272
00:18:03,350 --> 00:18:05,720
Mei, did you get a good look?

273
00:18:05,830 --> 00:18:06,640
Yes.

274
00:18:06,660 --> 00:18:08,060
Keep your head straight.

275
00:18:10,240 --> 00:18:12,830
Keep it. You can use it on the way.

276
00:18:15,220 --> 00:18:16,180
Where is my case?

277
00:18:16,650 --> 00:18:18,110
The one I asked you to hide.

278
00:18:38,440 --> 00:18:40,030
My Commander-in-chief entrusted this to me before he died.

